North Korea’s foreign minister told the United Nations on Saturday that the ongoing sanctions are leading to growing distrust in the United States and that the country would in no case be able to unilaterally give up its nuclear weapons under such circumstances.
Ri Yong Ho told the UN’s annual General Assembly that North Korea had taken “important goodwill measures” over the past year, such as halting nuclear and missile tests, dismantling the site for nuclear tests, and promising not to distribute nuclear weapons and nuclear technology.
