China and Russia believe that the UN Security Council should reward Pyongyang for the steps taken.
U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo told the U.N. Security Council on Thursday, “The enforcement of the Security Council’s sanctions must continue vigorously and reliably until we have achieved the full, final, verified denuclearization.”
Since 2006, the Security Council has unanimously imposed sanctions against North Korea to significantly reduce funding for Pyongyang’s nuclear and ballistic missile programs.
